Saedi et al. [22] extracted two natural dyes (NDs) from marine seaweed, red Gracilaria and green Ulva algae, and used them to form nanocomposites with GQD and use the nanocomposites as photosensitizers in DSSCs. The DSSC with GQD-Gracilaria reported an efficiency higher than other organic solar cells. Since it achieved 0.94% power conversion efficiency (

                           η

